1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:03,080
We gave up on the divorce.

2
00:00:05,680 --> 00:00:07,016
In fact, we’re having a wedding soon.

3
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:08,240
That’s what I’m talking about!

4
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:10,320
Son, thank God. I knew it.

5
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:13,480
This revenge wasn’t
only yours. It was ours.

6
00:00:14,040 --> 00:00:16,440
That man shattered my family.

7
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,920
Haydar will receive the
punishment he deserves.

8
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:20,200
Sooner or later.

9
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:23,040
But as I said before...

10
00:00:23,840 --> 00:00:26,040
Mercan is my red line.

11
00:00:26,520 --> 00:00:29,960
No matter what I say, I
won’t change your mind, will I?

12
00:00:30,360 --> 00:00:32,400
Meanwhile, your girl will
not stay in this mansion.

13
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:35,040
I want her gone as soon as possible.

14
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,480
Please give me a little more time, Ateş.

15
00:00:38,360 --> 00:00:42,040
Kiss the hand, my girl.
Don’t you know your manners?

16
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:44,480
Since you’re not divorcing.

17
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:51,920
Forget Mercan.

18
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:55,280
Even if they had divorced, she
would never have been with you.

19
00:00:56,080 --> 00:00:59,200
How many times have I told you
not to tell me this nonsense?

20
00:00:59,840 --> 00:01:01,080
How could you do that?

21
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:03,120
Didn’t you think of me at all?

22
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:04,600
Ateş refuses to give up.

23
00:01:05,520 --> 00:01:09,360
She’s the daughter of my father’s killer.

24
00:01:10,040 --> 00:01:12,600
You put dozens of people on
boats and sent them to their deaths.

25
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:16,480
You caused the deaths of dozens of people.

26
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,880
They were desperate, hopeless people.

27
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:21,640
They would have suffered
wherever they went anyway.

28
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:25,560
Do you decide who lives and who dies?

29
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:29,400
This world belongs to men who
have the power to decide, Ateş.

30
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:31,760
And I am one of those powerful men.

31
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:34,760
Haydar Yıldırım.

32
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:36,920
You are under arrest.

33
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:39,880
Human trafficking and causing
death through premeditation.

34
00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:40,600
What is happening?

35
00:01:40,601 --> 00:01:41,640
Don’t resist!

36
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:46,080
What we heard is enough to keep
him in prison for life, Mr. Ateş.

37
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:49,160
You helped him set a trap for your father.

38
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:52,120
You wanted that trap to
be set for your father.

39
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:53,720
Let go!

40
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:56,480
All of you will answer for this.

41
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:57,920
Let go!

42
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:00,600
Take your hands off me!

43
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:06,200
You've been on this journey with
Ates and Mercan from the very beginning.

44
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:09,520
Every twist, every
heartbreak. Every moment.

45
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:12,359
And now we reach the end.

46
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:14,279
This isn't something to watch alone.

47
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:16,599
This is something we experience together.

48
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:22,160
Episodes 98, 99 and 100 will not
be available on any memberships.

49
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:25,720
They will premiere on YouTube
for all of us at the same time.

50
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:27,239
One moment.

51
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:30,119
One story. One ending.

52
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:32,679
So grab your comfy
blanket and a huge bucket

53
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:35,680
of popcorn for one final twist.

54
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,760
Let's be there together.

55
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,840
You know I was reborn with you, don't you…

56
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:53,080
Before you, there was
only darkness in my life.

57
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,280
I couldn't see anything good or beautiful.

58
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:02,440
I didn't want to see either…

59
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:08,160
You reminded me that I had a heart.

60
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:14,840
You taught me that heart could love.

61
00:04:19,280 --> 00:04:20,280
That's why…

62
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:23,720
I'm not giving you a ring,

63
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:34,320
I'm giving you my heart,
which you reconciled with life.

64
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:40,600
When I wake up in the morning,

65
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:43,400
and when I watch the stars at night,

66
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:47,080
and when I grow old, I want you by my side.

67
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:53,680
Because now, there's only you…

68
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:01,760
Let's live this life you
made me love, together, Mercan.

69
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:08,280
I've loved you since the
moment I first saw you…

70
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:16,120
And I will love you until
the last moment of my life.

71
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,520
And what about you, Mercan Karahan?

72
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:57,120
Will you walk hand in hand,

73
00:05:58,480 --> 00:05:59,840
side by side with me for eternity?

74
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:09,320
I...

75
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:12,720
I am not just by your side.

76
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:20,800
I'm here…

77
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:32,160
And you are here.

78
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:40,720
We are each other's destiny.

79
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:50,880
We are each other's… heart.

80
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:54,440
That's why…

81
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:59,240
For eternity, a thousand times yes.

82
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,560
I love you.

83
00:07:40,840 --> 00:07:41,840
I love you.

84
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,560
Please, let's never
wake up from this dream.

85
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:05,760
We won't wake up.

86
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,840
Our whole life will be this dream.

87
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:52,680
The mothers' argument was bad, wasn't it…

88
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,720
If only that was it…

89
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,000
Çiçek...

90
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,240
My father is very sick.

91
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:06,320
Because I'm not with them...

92
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:09,320
they've been hiding it
from me for a long time.

93
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:15,160
Malik… I'm so sorry.

94
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,520
Did you call your father?

95
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,520
So many times…

96
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:21,960
But he's not answering.

97
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:25,400
When it's like this, I
get even more worried.

98
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:31,960
-Çiçek... -Hmm?

99
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:37,720
I need to go to Egypt as soon
as possible to see my father.

100
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:43,680
No matter how much we argue,
no matter how much we disagree...

101
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,200
he is my father.

102
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:47,400
I'm scared.

103
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:51,520
If something happens to him
before I can see him, God forbid...

104
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:54,480
I would never forgive myself.

105
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:59,760
You're right, you need to see your father.

106
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:03,280
My love...

107
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:10,800
I'll go and I'll come back
after healing my father.

108
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:12,560
I won't be long.

109
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:17,680
You know I can't live without you, right…?

110
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:19,640
I know.

111
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:22,360
Don't be sad.

112
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:26,240
Don't think about me now,
think about your father.

113
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:29,936
I'm sure he'll recover as soon as he
sees you, he'll get better right away.

114
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:31,120
You'll be good for him.

115
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:34,560
I'm glad I have you.

116
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:36,880
Me too.

117
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:58,160
Where is Burak? Our
folks will be here soon.

118
00:10:58,440 --> 00:10:59,920
He'll be here, don't worry.

119
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:02,640
-Ah, he's here. -I'm here.

120
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:06,640
-So, where is it? -Where is what?

121
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,960
He forgot the cake. Where's the cake?

122
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:14,400
Oh no! I forgot it!

123
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:19,520
What do we do?

124
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:23,880
They're already here.

125
00:11:24,040 --> 00:11:26,120
-Why are you in the dark? -Surprise!

126
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,720
Turn on the light, come on!

127
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,720
Goodness, we tried to surprise you.

128
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,040
What's going on here?

129
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:42,440
We were going to surprise
you with a celebration cake.

130
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:45,200
Our friend forgot the cake
and only brought himself.

131
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:51,799
Sorry, I'll go get it right away.

132
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:54,640
Wait, Burak! No hurry. It's done now.

133
00:11:58,040 --> 00:12:00,000
Yeah. It's not necessary anyway.

134
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:01,560
Oh, you poor thing.

135
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,440
Congratulations.

136
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:13,280
Cemal just told me about tonight's event.

137
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:15,120
You're quite something, really.

138
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:19,240
It turned out well. My brave brother!

139
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:22,960
Congratulations! Be very happy. My dear.

140
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:27,840
They might have been
happier if there was cake.

141
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:37,000
No words against my brother.
He might have forgotten.

142
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,200
Of course. No words against Burak.

143
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:40,600
He'll have much more to do.

144
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:45,000
Let everything be complete,
let it be done properly.

145
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:50,280
Now that the proposal is done,
next is… the asking for her hand.

146
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:55,720
As the groom's family, we are excited.

147
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:58,160
Ateş...

148
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:01,800
My daughter-in-law will
have everything done properly.

149
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:04,760
There will be the asking ceremony,

150
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:06,360
the henna night,

151
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:09,400
the wedding, and the
honeymoon. No objections.

152
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:14,360
But is all this necessary?

153
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:16,800
Yes.

154
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:19,640
I entered your life by force.

155
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,200
By hurting you.

156
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:25,040
Now I will do everything
from the very beginning.

157
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,640
But this time, by making you happy.

158
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:33,000
I want to erase all
the bad memories, Mercan.

159
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,160
You'll give me this chance, right?

160
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:39,520
Good.

161
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:41,960
Then tell your mother...

162
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:45,000
we are coming to ask for
her daughter's hand tomorrow.

163
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,280
Very classy move.

164
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:49,680
He's a real gentleman.

165
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:52,440
That's how we are, hope you don't mind.

166
00:13:57,800 --> 00:13:58,800
So?

167
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:00,840
You're saying tomorrow...

168
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,360
How will I prepare myself?

169
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:06,240
I... I should go.

170
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:07,840
Wait, I'll drop you off.

171
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:09,080
-Okay. -Let's go.

172
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:13,880
I might as well go too.

173
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:15,600
Burak...

174
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:18,840
Thanks for being by my side.

175
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,280
Always.

176
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:26,320
It would have been better if I
hadn't forgotten the cake though.

177
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:28,040
It's okay.

178
00:14:28,680 --> 00:14:29,880
-Goodnight then! -Goodnight.

179
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:36,400
I...

180
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:37,880
thank you very much.

181
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:40,080
I mean, for being so thoughtful.

182
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:44,200
But you know our circumstances…

183
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:46,560
We really don't need all this.

184
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:49,120
I think we've torn up those circumstances.

185
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:51,880
Like I said...

186
00:14:52,640 --> 00:14:54,240
Everything will be done from scratch.

187
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,880
And you, stop saying it's not necessary.

188
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,480
Start enjoying it...

189
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,920
We'll start a brand new life together.

190
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:11,520
You and me...

191
00:15:15,640 --> 00:15:16,640
I'll be there soon.

192
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:39,240
No, no, no.

193
00:15:42,160 --> 00:15:43,600
You know, those pearl earrings...

194
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:45,840
the big ones, you know?

195
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:48,320
Are you sure you haven't seen them?

196
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:50,920
Really, Mrs. [Müzeyyen
Mother], I haven't seen them.

197
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:53,240
Did Nermin come into my room at all?

198
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:56,120
I don't know what to say.

199
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:58,280
Mrs. Nermin was out all day too.

200
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:00,720
So where did these earrings fly off to?

201
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:06,680
Maybe they fell into your
pocket by mistake, check, will you?

202
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:10,720
How could such a thing happen…

203
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:12,880
All these years... I…

204
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:16,456
I wouldn't do such a thing, Mrs.
[Müzeyyen Mother], don't you know me?

205
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:17,800
What's going on, Müzeyyen Mother?

206
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:22,360
I can't find something where it should be.

207
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:29,000
Don't break the girl's heart.

208
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:32,400
Okay, I'll win her heart back tomorrow.

209
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:35,520
What's up, you don't
usually visit me at this hour?

210
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:38,960
We're going to ask for
Mercan's hand tomorrow.

211
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:40,800
What!

212
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:44,176
What asking, son, have you lost your mind!?

213
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:45,680
You're already married.

214
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:47,360
Look, Müzeyyen Mother.

215
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:49,720
We've been through difficult times.

216
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:51,560
We've hurt each other too.

217
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:53,840
But now I want us to get better.

218
00:16:54,640 --> 00:16:55,680
You want this too.

219
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:58,800
You want things to be
like they used to be...

220
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:02,000
Well, now there's a good
opportunity ahead of us.

221
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:04,120
Look, Haydar is in prison,

222
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:07,400
he got the punishment he
deserved. Isn't that what we wanted?

223
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:09,520
After everything that happened…

224
00:17:09,560 --> 00:17:11,280
Yes. Especially because of that.

225
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,320
Despite everything that happened…

226
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:15,480
I want us to have no more problems.

227
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:18,440
You're like a mother to me.

228
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:22,680
I can never repay you.

229
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:27,960
No one else deserves this but you.

230
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:32,800
You won't leave me alone, will you?

231
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:46,120
Alright.

232
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:49,480
Since you insist it has to be this way.

233
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:56,800
Goodnight.

234
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:58,400
Goodnight.

235
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:27,560
You said you had work. You
didn't let me do a surprise…

236
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:29,720
What surprise is this?

237
00:18:31,960 --> 00:18:34,960
I'm making you a celebration cake.

238
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:36,600
Hmm!

239
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:42,440
Orange cake.

240
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:46,920
My favorite. How did you know?

241
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:53,080
I have connections who do shady business.

242
00:18:57,560 --> 00:18:58,560
You mean Cemal…

243
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:02,160
Are you Sherlock Holmes or what?

244
00:19:10,360 --> 00:19:11,840
You had to do it, didn't you?

245
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:18,520
Well then...

246
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:22,920
You started the war.

247
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:25,520
Just wait...

248
00:19:26,480 --> 00:19:28,240
This kitchen will see many more wars.

249
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:30,640
If only it could talk.

250
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:32,200
Right?

251
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:36,160
Look... I'm going to
let go of your hands...

252
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:39,280
- But you won't smear it on my face.
- Hm-hmm.

253
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:41,520
-I'm letting go. -Okay.

254
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:43,280
Let go.

255
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:52,280
I was going to help you, though.

256
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:54,000
Like this kind of help, for instance…

257
00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:55,360
Exactly like this!

258
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:57,680
What are you doing! There you go!

259
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Take that!

260
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:24,360
And take this too!

261
00:20:43,520 --> 00:20:45,120
It was a sweet war, I think.

262
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:46,720
Very sweet...

263
00:20:47,840 --> 00:20:48,880
Let's always be like this.

264
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:50,600
Have no doubt about it.

265
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:15,080
-Malik. -Hmm?

266
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:18,800
I wrote down the missing items for the
mansion and garden. Do you need anything?

267
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:21,360
I also need a few things for the car.

268
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:23,880
Wax and glass cleaner.

269
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:26,520
-Glass cleaner. Okay. -Okay.

270
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:29,960
I'm so tired. Çiçek.

271
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:32,160
Come on dear, pour
some tea so we can drink.

272
00:21:33,280 --> 00:21:34,280
Okay, mom.

273
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:36,960
Alright, alright.

274
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:48,640
Zehra…

275
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:52,600
What's wrong, my wife?

276
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:06,080
It's nothing, it's okay, it's passed.

277
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:12,040
My wife is crying, how can it be nothing.

278
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:14,080
Come here.

279
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:15,760
Sit down.

280
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:20,040
Tell me what happened?

281
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,000
Why are you crying?

282
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:24,160
Müzeyyen Mother…

283
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:33,760
She accused me of theft.

284
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:39,480
She implied it, I mean…

285
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:43,320
She couldn't find her earrings…

286
00:22:47,040 --> 00:22:49,560
Look at what the woman I've
worked for, for years, said.

287
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:58,480
No, it really stings.

288
00:22:58,840 --> 00:23:00,960
Just because we're
employees, because we're poor,

289
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,400
does she think we covet
other people's property?

290
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,440
I can't get over it.

291
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:08,160
That's just her way.

292
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:12,200
The rich are always greedier than the poor.

293
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:17,480
Because their eyes are never satisfied
with wealth, they think we are like them.

294
00:23:23,040 --> 00:23:24,520
What kind of people are these.

295
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:26,320
It's shameful!

296
00:23:27,040 --> 00:23:28,040
Rude!

297
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:35,880
Don't cry, my wife. Wipe your tears.

298
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:38,920
Everyone has their own
sensitive spot, I guess.

299
00:23:44,520 --> 00:23:46,160
Because I grew up alone too,

300
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:48,240
things like this hurt my pride deeply.

301
00:23:55,120 --> 00:23:56,120
My mother...

302
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:01,960
My mother died.

303
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:18,880
My father left.

304
00:24:22,280 --> 00:24:24,440
I always lived like a
parasite in a relative's house.

305
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:35,320
It's hard.

306
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:42,320
You take a bite, and they stare at you.

307
00:24:45,680 --> 00:24:47,480
Then you get used to eating little.

308
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:56,960
You don't even turn on the
light in the room, to avoid gossip.

309
00:24:59,680 --> 00:25:01,440
I admit I'm not a very good person.

310
00:25:02,560 --> 00:25:04,640
But I've never let anyone
call me a thief either.

311
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:11,920
But...

312
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:16,560
When you have no one,
this is how it turns out.

313
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:33,000
No one...

314
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,920
Of course they know no
one will stand behind her.

315
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:45,920
My wife. Zehra.

316
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:48,040
What kind of talk is that!

317
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:51,400
You have a husband, my girl!

318
00:25:53,040 --> 00:25:55,280
Always! Look, your mother is here!

319
00:25:56,120 --> 00:25:58,560
Çiçek is here. Malik is here.

320
00:26:09,920 --> 00:26:12,360
We are behind you. Listen to me...

321
00:26:13,520 --> 00:26:14,520
Until death.

322
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:17,240
Zehra...

323
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:19,040
Well...

324
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:21,720
No matter how much we argue...

325
00:26:22,960 --> 00:26:24,440
we are daughters of the same house.

326
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:32,280
I am always by your side too. Don't be sad…

327
00:26:45,320 --> 00:26:46,320
Okay, come on...

328
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:48,240
Wipe those eyes now.

329
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:52,000
You won't shed tears for good or bad. Okay?

330
00:26:56,560 --> 00:26:58,640
Wipe those eyes now.

331
00:26:59,800 --> 00:27:00,800
Come on.

332
00:27:01,520 --> 00:27:02,520
Don't cry...

333
00:28:13,480 --> 00:28:15,560
Dry your hair, you'll get sick.

334
00:28:16,840 --> 00:28:18,160
Nothing will happen to me.

335
00:28:22,120 --> 00:28:23,400
Okay, wait. Wait.

336
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:28,280
This time, you'll listen to me.

337
00:28:29,840 --> 00:28:30,960
Wait, let me get a towel.

338
00:28:51,920 --> 00:28:53,400
You've learned this cooking business.

339
00:28:54,680 --> 00:28:57,400
It was the best cake I've ever eaten.

340
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:00,920
I figured from you
eating four slices anyway.

341
00:29:01,720 --> 00:29:04,280
It's because these
beautiful hands touched it.

342
00:29:05,680 --> 00:29:07,360
My wife turned out to be very talented.

343
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:10,920
Make me a promise.

344
00:29:14,120 --> 00:29:15,600
When I grow old,

345
00:29:16,240 --> 00:29:17,760
when my back is bent like this…

346
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:21,480
promise you'll love me like this
even when I can't make orange cake.

347
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:27,400
I made you a promise today.

348
00:29:28,240 --> 00:29:30,280
Not for three years or five years,

349
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:32,200
my promise is for a lifetime.

350
00:29:33,320 --> 00:29:34,320
And the cake…

351
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:36,520
if you can't make it, I'll make it.

352
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:40,360
Just you looking at me
sweetly like this is enough.

353
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:45,000
I'm so happy.

354
00:29:46,120 --> 00:29:47,120
I'm so lucky…

355
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:51,120
You or me…

356
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:52,840
Me, of course.

357
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:54,560
No, me.

358
00:29:55,680 --> 00:29:56,680
I said, me.

359
00:29:58,600 --> 00:29:59,840
Okay, you.

360
00:30:01,440 --> 00:30:02,440
You are everything.

361
00:30:14,200 --> 00:30:15,600
Your hair smells so good.

362
00:30:17,240 --> 00:30:19,120
And you smell like orange cake.

363
00:31:58,440 --> 00:32:00,080
You seem to have gotten used to fighting.

364
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:13,720
We're going to ask for your hand today.

365
00:32:20,520 --> 00:32:22,200
Are you really ready to become my wife?

366
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:27,600
I'm ready.

367
00:32:35,640 --> 00:32:38,800
But... we have a lot to do, get up.

368
00:32:39,400 --> 00:32:40,400
Come on, get up!

369
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:43,360
You're going to leave the room
and go downstairs to the living room.

370
00:32:43,560 --> 00:32:44,560
What's the hurry?

371
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:46,440
Really.

372
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:50,520
You're going to seriously ask for
my hand even though we're married.

373
00:32:51,680 --> 00:32:53,640
But still, there's a lot to do.

374
00:32:54,800 --> 00:32:55,800
Stay in bed, rest.

375
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:58,720
Actually, let's stay in bed all day.

376
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:02,880
Just look at me like this,
in your most beautiful light.

377
00:33:06,360 --> 00:33:09,056
I think you should get used to hearing
beautiful things from your husband.

378
00:33:09,080 --> 00:33:10,920
Because I'll never stop saying them.

379
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:16,681
I spoke with Müzeyyen Mother,
she will ask for your hand.

380
00:33:18,680 --> 00:33:19,760
How did she accept?

381
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:23,120
Everything will fall into place, slowly.

382
00:33:24,880 --> 00:33:28,000
Our love is strong
enough to fix everything.

383
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:31,640
I trust you.

384
00:33:33,440 --> 00:33:34,440
But...

385
00:33:34,720 --> 00:33:37,120
Müzeyyen Mother accepting so quickly

386
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:39,000
makes one a bit suspicious.

387
00:33:40,200 --> 00:33:41,560
She doesn't have a plan, does she?

388
00:33:42,880 --> 00:33:44,240
No one can do anything.

389
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:46,920
Whoever does will face the consequences.

390
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:12,040
Come on, bring them in. It's
breakfast time, we're late.

391
00:34:22,520 --> 00:34:23,920
I've looked everywhere.

392
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:28,720
No one else enters my room besides you.

393
00:34:29,600 --> 00:34:32,120
Tell me, where did you
hide the earrings, you thief!

394
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:35,000
Mind your place, Müzeyyen Mother!

395
00:34:38,200 --> 00:34:39,920
Müzeyyen Mother, please!

396
00:34:44,080 --> 00:34:46,560
Well, birds of a feather
flock together, of course!

397
00:34:47,240 --> 00:34:48,240
Müzeyyen Mother!

398
00:34:49,160 --> 00:34:51,840
I've worked for you for years,
what fault have you seen in me!

399
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:54,920
I've been patient, and now I
decide to steal your belongings!

400
00:34:55,400 --> 00:34:57,520
I've worked and earned
with my labor until today.

401
00:34:58,280 --> 00:35:01,000
I didn't deserve this
insult! You are wrong!

402
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:02,840
Oh, really!

403
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:05,360
Am I going to learn
right from wrong from you!

404
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:12,480
Who do you think you
are, answering me back!

405
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:17,720
You will stop right there, Müzeyyen Mother!

406
00:35:21,320 --> 00:35:22,600
Zehra is my daughter-in-law.

407
00:35:27,040 --> 00:35:28,240
I stand behind her.

408
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:31,480
If she says she didn't
take them, she didn't.

409
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:36,520
If you raise your hand against
the helpless, it will anger God.

410
00:35:38,040 --> 00:35:40,280
Maybe we can't stand up to you.

411
00:35:41,560 --> 00:35:43,800
We are beneath you. Fine.

412
00:35:52,600 --> 00:35:54,000
But God is greater than us all.

413
00:36:01,040 --> 00:36:02,800
He does not ignore the
cry of the oppressed.

414
00:36:04,120 --> 00:36:06,760
I finish my own work, now I
have to deal with the riffraff?

415
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:08,960
Do whatever you want!

416
00:36:23,680 --> 00:36:24,680
Thank you…

417
00:36:26,080 --> 00:36:27,080
Mother.

418
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:37,320
For the first time, someone
is standing up for me.

419
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:46,560
For the first time, I didn't feel alone.

420
00:36:50,960 --> 00:36:51,960
Thank you… my daughter.

421
00:37:03,880 --> 00:37:06,000
Come here. Come here, you.

422
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:30,960
What happened?

423
00:37:40,560 --> 00:37:41,680
I have another daughter now.

424
00:37:43,680 --> 00:37:45,120
Our family has grown.

425
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:52,040
Come.

426
00:37:54,720 --> 00:37:56,120
I've never seen anything like this.

427
00:38:17,040 --> 00:38:18,040
Mother...

428
00:38:25,880 --> 00:38:26,880
Today...

429
00:38:28,080 --> 00:38:30,200
Müzeyyen Mother is going
to ask for my hand from you.

430
00:38:32,440 --> 00:38:33,440
What?

431
00:38:36,720 --> 00:38:38,840
Ateş wants to start everything over.

432
00:38:40,120 --> 00:38:41,520
To mend what he broke…

433
00:38:46,200 --> 00:38:48,360
Two people who love each other...

434
00:38:48,800 --> 00:38:50,480
he says we will do everything

435
00:38:50,880 --> 00:38:52,200
that's done when getting married.

436
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:55,760
Oh, well. Okay.

437
00:39:00,080 --> 00:39:02,120
That woman is going to
ask for you from me, huh?

438
00:39:03,960 --> 00:39:05,160
It's God's will, I suppose.

439
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:07,960
Mother, please.

440
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:11,680
Okay, my daughter. Okay.

441
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:16,560
If only...

442
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:20,920
if only my father were a proper person,

443
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:24,280
he would be by my side today too.

444
00:39:28,560 --> 00:39:29,560
If only...

445
00:39:30,320 --> 00:39:31,320
If only...

446
00:39:33,440 --> 00:39:34,520
But look...

447
00:39:36,440 --> 00:39:38,120
Your father did wrong things, okay.

448
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:43,200
He obtained this wealth through
bad means, okay, I accept that too.

449
00:39:45,720 --> 00:39:50,400
But you studied and lived a
comfortable life thanks to this wealth.

450
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:54,000
I mean...

451
00:39:54,320 --> 00:39:56,880
Does that mean I have to
overlook the wrongdoings?

452
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:09,360
If only I were poor...

453
00:40:11,600 --> 00:40:13,520
so my father wouldn't
have done these bad things

454
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:15,760
and would be by my side.

455
00:40:16,640 --> 00:40:19,640
Maybe he'd be here now, and we'd be happy.

456
00:40:22,200 --> 00:40:23,360
If only my brother too...

457
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:27,800
could have managed to be a decent person.

458
00:40:29,200 --> 00:40:30,400
He would be by my side today.

459
00:40:37,920 --> 00:40:38,920
If only you too...

460
00:40:40,240 --> 00:40:42,280
instead of expensive jewels,

461
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:44,560
you had worn wooden beads,

462
00:40:45,680 --> 00:40:47,560
and been a more
compassionate, loving mother.

463
00:40:52,920 --> 00:40:53,920
Mercan...

464
00:40:55,520 --> 00:40:57,320
Look, I know.

465
00:40:58,720 --> 00:41:01,200
It's not just your father
and brother who made mistakes.

466
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:04,280
I made them too.

467
00:41:06,640 --> 00:41:07,640
But...

468
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:10,520
We're human, we did things.

469
00:41:13,960 --> 00:41:16,320
We always knew how to get
back up from where we fell.

470
00:41:16,560 --> 00:41:17,720
That's how we've always been.

471
00:41:18,280 --> 00:41:19,360
We'll get up again.

472
00:41:22,840 --> 00:41:24,440
Okay, okay.

473
00:41:25,920 --> 00:41:28,240
I won't be the one causing
trouble, don't worry.

474
00:41:32,080 --> 00:41:33,080
Come here, you.

475
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:46,320
Mother.

476
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:49,280
Burak will also be by my side.

477
00:41:50,200 --> 00:41:52,160
I expect understanding from you.

478
00:41:54,360 --> 00:41:55,360
Okay.

479
00:41:55,560 --> 00:41:56,760
If you say so...

480
00:41:58,400 --> 00:42:00,720
Mothers do anything for their daughters.

481
00:42:02,040 --> 00:42:05,560
Let's turn over a new
leaf, mother and daughter.

482
00:42:06,160 --> 00:42:07,600
A brand new page.

483
00:42:10,640 --> 00:42:13,240
But I don't trust Müzeyyen.

484
00:42:14,360 --> 00:42:15,360
Like I said...

485
00:42:15,680 --> 00:42:17,400
That woman is a devil.

486
00:42:19,160 --> 00:42:21,400
If I am bad, she is a
thousand times worse than me.

487
00:42:23,080 --> 00:42:24,360
Yes. Believe me.

488
00:42:35,360 --> 00:42:37,720
Tell me in detail, what happened?

489
00:42:40,320 --> 00:42:42,880
First, she implied that I took them.

490
00:42:44,080 --> 00:42:47,160
She literally came at me,
openly calling me a thief.

491
00:42:48,960 --> 00:42:50,040
What kind of woman is this!

492
00:42:50,920 --> 00:42:52,360
What a shameless woman.

493
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:55,880
Who is she to call my wife a thief.

494
00:42:58,080 --> 00:43:00,920
-Let her say it to me! -Wait, Berat! Don't.

495
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:03,040
No way, that's nonsense!

496
00:43:03,520 --> 00:43:04,520
What do you mean "Don't"?

497
00:43:04,720 --> 00:43:06,040
-Just wait! -Berat!

498
00:43:06,600 --> 00:43:08,080
Don't get yourself in trouble.

499
00:43:09,160 --> 00:43:10,840
You've never seen real trouble, my girl.

500
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:13,240
I'll show her what trouble is.

501
00:43:14,000 --> 00:43:15,320
That woman called you a thief.

502
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:17,280
She slandered your name.

503
00:43:18,120 --> 00:43:19,720
She's going to make me have a breakdown.

504
00:43:22,680 --> 00:43:25,600
Binnaz Mother gave her a piece of her mind.

505
00:43:29,080 --> 00:43:30,600
Even Çiçek stood behind me.

506
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:36,920
Now you're standing up
for me, risking everything.

507
00:43:38,400 --> 00:43:39,920
That's enough for me, Berat.

508
00:43:41,680 --> 00:43:43,120
Please, let's not cause any trouble.

509
00:43:49,120 --> 00:43:51,120
You are truly good people.

510
00:43:53,200 --> 00:43:57,920
You stood by me, even at
the risk of losing your jobs.

511
00:44:01,520 --> 00:44:02,680
I'll never forget this.

512
00:44:08,640 --> 00:44:09,640
I...

513
00:44:11,000 --> 00:44:12,040
Today, for the first time…

514
00:44:14,120 --> 00:44:15,560
for the first time in my life,

515
00:44:16,920 --> 00:44:18,680
I felt like I had a real family.

516
00:44:39,560 --> 00:44:40,560
My wife.

517
00:44:41,240 --> 00:44:43,880
We didn't put that ring on for a joke.

518
00:44:45,160 --> 00:44:46,160
Do you understand?

519
00:44:47,560 --> 00:44:48,560
The one who...

520
00:44:49,200 --> 00:44:51,240
The one who called you a thief... I will...

521
00:44:51,920 --> 00:44:53,120
destroy their world.

522
00:44:54,120 --> 00:44:55,120
Destroy it.

523
00:44:56,520 --> 00:44:57,760
No one can stop me.

524
00:44:58,880 --> 00:45:01,240
I'll burn everything to the ground.

525
00:45:02,280 --> 00:45:04,280
Okay? My dear.

526
00:45:06,000 --> 00:45:07,800
-My dear husband. -I'll destroy them.

527
00:45:08,680 --> 00:45:10,240
Come on, we're going to work.

528
00:45:14,040 --> 00:45:15,040
Anyway...

529
00:45:25,520 --> 00:45:26,520
Mrs. Binnaz...

530
00:45:27,160 --> 00:45:29,160
Should we put the
refreshments on this side?

531
00:45:29,240 --> 00:45:30,840
Let's put them, my girl, let's put them.

532
00:45:32,800 --> 00:45:36,840
If only my Murat were
alive to see these days.

533
00:45:40,040 --> 00:45:42,000
He was so sweet when he
was a child, wasn't he?

534
00:45:53,680 --> 00:45:54,680
Mrs. Nermin...

535
00:45:55,200 --> 00:45:57,560
I think this flower
doesn't look right here?

536
00:45:58,640 --> 00:45:59,800
I don't think it looks right.

537
00:46:02,680 --> 00:46:05,680
Leave it over there.

538
00:46:06,600 --> 00:46:07,600
Okay.

539
00:46:10,440 --> 00:46:11,440
How is this?

540
00:46:12,080 --> 00:46:13,080
Very nice.

541
00:46:15,640 --> 00:46:16,640
Mercan.

542
00:46:18,040 --> 00:46:19,400
Are you excited?

543
00:46:21,040 --> 00:46:22,240
I'm excited too.

544
00:46:22,920 --> 00:46:28,120
If there's anything you want
from me for tonight, don't hesitate.

545
00:46:28,640 --> 00:46:30,120
Your happiness is my happiness.

546
00:46:30,440 --> 00:46:31,919
Thanks, Cemal.

547
00:46:31,920 --> 00:46:34,840
Don't need anything for now,
but if I do, I'll find you.

548
00:46:39,320 --> 00:46:40,400
There it is!

549
00:46:43,560 --> 00:46:46,400
The tray! But not just any tray…

550
00:46:46,680 --> 00:46:49,280
The tray our bride-to-be
will serve the coffees on!

551
00:46:52,880 --> 00:46:54,960
Demet… It's beautiful! Thank you.

552
00:46:58,480 --> 00:46:59,480
You like it?

553
00:46:59,840 --> 00:47:00,840
Yes.

554
00:47:01,760 --> 00:47:02,840
Mrs. Mercan!

555
00:47:03,480 --> 00:47:05,920
Shall we take one last look
at the food menu together…

556
00:47:06,320 --> 00:47:08,240
-Okay, coming. -Wait.

557
00:47:08,880 --> 00:47:11,480
Let me take a look too, you
wouldn't understand anyway.

558
00:47:14,720 --> 00:47:15,960
Demet, I want to say something.

559
00:47:16,200 --> 00:47:19,760
Are you sure you're Nezir's sister?

560
00:47:20,440 --> 00:47:21,960
While Nezir is so selfish, you...

561
00:47:22,640 --> 00:47:23,640
Cemal...

562
00:47:24,360 --> 00:47:26,120
Let's speak properly about my brother.

563
00:47:26,840 --> 00:47:28,560
What did I say? I said selfish.

564
00:47:29,040 --> 00:47:30,040
Don't say that.

565
00:47:30,920 --> 00:47:34,000
Actually, my intention wasn't to
put him down, but to praise you.

566
00:47:35,560 --> 00:47:37,320
If I could have finished my sentence,

567
00:47:38,680 --> 00:47:42,000
I was going to say you
have a beautiful, big heart.

568
00:47:46,760 --> 00:47:48,360
It doesn't mean much now, of course.

569
00:47:54,840 --> 00:47:56,240
I… let me take this!

570
00:47:56,960 --> 00:47:58,160
Go ahead, take it.

571
00:48:22,120 --> 00:48:23,120
My daughter.

572
00:48:24,400 --> 00:48:25,520
Come on now.

573
00:48:25,720 --> 00:48:28,360
Sit up, my girl. Eat a couple of bites…

574
00:48:30,760 --> 00:48:31,760
Be careful.

575
00:48:41,800 --> 00:48:42,960
How are you today?

576
00:48:44,800 --> 00:48:46,040
Like a trash can…

577
00:48:47,280 --> 00:48:49,040
I don't have the strength to lift my hand.

578
00:48:49,880 --> 00:48:51,240
I'm constantly sleepy.

579
00:48:51,880 --> 00:48:53,320
I don't understand what's happening…

580
00:48:54,680 --> 00:48:58,320
Well, all this stress
has to manifest somewhere.

581
00:48:59,600 --> 00:49:01,080
And it's the change of season…

582
00:49:01,960 --> 00:49:03,040
That affects it too.

583
00:49:03,480 --> 00:49:06,240
You need to rest for a while, I guess.

584
00:49:06,280 --> 00:49:07,400
Your body is asking for it.

585
00:49:11,360 --> 00:49:12,360
Where is Ateş?

586
00:49:13,600 --> 00:49:15,160
Why isn't he visiting me?

587
00:49:16,000 --> 00:49:18,040
He's very busy, my
daughter. Running around.

588
00:49:22,760 --> 00:49:23,760
Come in.

589
00:49:29,240 --> 00:49:32,560
Mrs. Müzeyyen, the dress you wanted for
tonight has arrived. I put it in your room.

590
00:49:37,480 --> 00:49:40,241
Çiçek is also making preparations
downstairs for the asking ceremony.

591
00:49:40,560 --> 00:49:42,600
Mrs. Demet also came to help.

592
00:49:43,080 --> 00:49:44,080
Okay, get out!

593
00:49:48,800 --> 00:49:49,800
What asking ceremony?

594
00:49:50,160 --> 00:49:51,160
Eat your soup.

595
00:49:52,000 --> 00:49:54,160
What's going on, mother!
What is this asking ceremony!

596
00:49:54,280 --> 00:49:56,040
I said you need to rest.

597
00:49:57,440 --> 00:49:59,680
There's going to be an
asking ceremony for that girl.

598
00:50:00,280 --> 00:50:03,120
You're trying to distract
me with tea and soup.

599
00:50:05,040 --> 00:50:06,760
-My daughter... -Leave, mother.

600
00:50:07,920 --> 00:50:08,920
Get out of my room!

601
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:36,000
What happened?

602
00:50:37,080 --> 00:50:38,080
You were quiet.

603
00:50:39,520 --> 00:50:41,360
You are such a useless man.

604
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:44,520
What are you saying! Watch your mouth!

605
00:50:46,080 --> 00:50:49,360
If you had done what you needed
to do instead of messing with me,

606
00:50:49,760 --> 00:50:51,240
we wouldn't be in this state.

607
00:50:57,000 --> 00:50:58,880
Ateş is going to ask
for Mercan's hand tonight!

608
00:50:59,280 --> 00:51:01,080
And your sister is here
as the maid of honor!

609
00:51:03,120 --> 00:51:04,120
Asking for her hand!

610
00:51:06,800 --> 00:51:07,840
What is Demet doing there?

611
00:51:09,760 --> 00:51:11,840
Helping her best friend.

612
00:51:12,520 --> 00:51:13,520
Go back to sleepwalking.

613
00:51:17,040 --> 00:51:20,520
If you keep this up, you'll only manage
to give a single gold coin as a gift.

614
00:51:24,440 --> 00:51:25,440
Idiot!

615
00:51:28,240 --> 00:51:29,240
Damn it!

616
00:51:30,640 --> 00:51:31,720
Damn it!

617
00:51:34,880 --> 00:51:35,880
I won't allow it!

618
00:51:38,320 --> 00:51:39,840
You won't be able to do it!

619
00:51:40,600 --> 00:51:42,080
I'll show you all!

620
00:52:08,320 --> 00:52:10,160
You panicked… what are you hiding?

621
00:52:11,000 --> 00:52:12,640
I bought a beautiful dress for tonight…

622
00:52:14,200 --> 00:52:15,760
But you can't see it now.

623
00:52:16,440 --> 00:52:17,440
When the time comes…

624
00:52:18,200 --> 00:52:19,200
Actually...

625
00:52:22,400 --> 00:52:23,400
Look.

626
00:52:24,120 --> 00:52:25,640
I also prepared a suit for you.

627
00:52:26,040 --> 00:52:27,040
How is it?

628
00:52:27,880 --> 00:52:29,720
Hmm… Thank you very much.

629
00:52:30,160 --> 00:52:31,800
But maybe I'll wear something else.

630
00:52:33,840 --> 00:52:34,840
Oh, really...

631
00:52:36,000 --> 00:52:37,880
When did you even arrange the suit?

632
00:52:40,080 --> 00:52:42,720
I handle a lot of things
without you noticing.

633
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:45,320
Is that so?

634
00:52:46,280 --> 00:52:47,280
Yes.

635
00:52:47,960 --> 00:52:48,960
Okay.

636
00:52:54,520 --> 00:52:56,440
For example, right now you want to hug me.

637
00:52:57,080 --> 00:52:59,440
See, I'm handling that immediately…

638
00:53:07,080 --> 00:53:09,480
I'm so afraid something
will go wrong tonight.

639
00:53:10,400 --> 00:53:11,400
Don't worry.

640
00:53:12,480 --> 00:53:13,880
Everything is under control.

641
00:53:17,440 --> 00:53:18,800
Let's say they refuse.

642
00:53:20,040 --> 00:53:21,640
I'll sweep you up and elope with you.

643
00:53:22,400 --> 00:53:23,640
Everything is planned.

644
00:53:24,840 --> 00:53:26,880
I still can't believe what we're doing.

645
00:53:28,080 --> 00:53:30,280
I don't know if it's a game or a dream…

646
00:53:30,600 --> 00:53:31,840
But I'm so excited.

647
00:53:32,960 --> 00:53:33,960
It's real.

648
00:53:35,160 --> 00:53:36,600
The most beautiful reality, at that…

649
00:53:42,120 --> 00:53:43,400
Mercan, come on...

650
00:53:44,080 --> 00:53:46,520
You need to come downstairs.
Regarding the preparations.

651
00:53:47,600 --> 00:53:48,600
Okay.

652
00:53:52,160 --> 00:53:54,680
Come on, don't dawdle, get ready quickly.

653
00:53:55,520 --> 00:53:57,960
You're wearing the suit I gave
you tonight, just so you know.

654
00:53:59,320 --> 00:54:00,320
On one condition…

655
00:54:04,080 --> 00:54:05,720
Don't put salt in the coffee.

656
00:54:08,200 --> 00:54:09,680
Are you afraid of getting burned?

657
00:54:11,480 --> 00:54:12,600
I'm already burned.

658
00:54:14,960 --> 00:54:16,040
I'm not promising.

659
00:54:17,200 --> 00:54:18,960
Besides, I think you
shouldn't overthink it.

660
00:54:19,360 --> 00:54:21,520
He who thinks about the
consequences cannot be a hero.

661
00:54:33,960 --> 00:54:36,720
As if you wouldn't drink
it even if it were poison…

662
00:54:57,480 --> 00:55:01,000
I will not let my child fall into
the hands of fortune hunters like you.

663
00:55:01,560 --> 00:55:02,840
You'll be waiting a long time.

664
00:55:16,680 --> 00:55:20,520
I called my father like 20
times. He's not answering…

665
00:55:23,600 --> 00:55:25,440
Well… he's resentful, son.

666
00:55:26,680 --> 00:55:28,040
The man is very sick...

667
00:55:29,000 --> 00:55:31,360
Just calling from afar to
say get well soon isn't enough.

668
00:55:32,400 --> 00:55:35,520
You need to kiss his hand
and ask for his forgiveness.

669
00:55:36,960 --> 00:55:37,960
God forbid…

670
00:55:38,480 --> 00:55:39,480
God forbid…

671
00:55:41,240 --> 00:55:43,400
(God give him health, God
willing he recovers quickly)

672
00:55:44,480 --> 00:55:45,480
I've thought it over.

673
00:55:47,120 --> 00:55:48,320
I will come with you to Egypt.

674
00:55:48,560 --> 00:55:50,360
Ah, thank God.

675
00:55:50,960 --> 00:55:51,960
Thank God.

676
00:55:54,160 --> 00:55:57,080
-(May God be pleased with you) -(May
God be pleased with you too, my son)

677
00:56:08,200 --> 00:56:11,040
Okay, don't you worry. God
willing, we will find a cure. Okay?

678
00:56:20,600 --> 00:56:24,160
Let me just get you to
Egypt, the rest is easy.

679
00:57:09,560 --> 00:57:11,000
Is everything ready, kids?

680
00:57:11,040 --> 00:57:12,240
All preparations are complete.

681
00:57:12,280 --> 00:57:13,840
Exactly as you wanted.

682
00:57:14,200 --> 00:57:15,360
Nothing missing, right?

683
00:57:15,680 --> 00:57:16,680
No, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

684
00:57:19,000 --> 00:57:20,560
You went to so much trouble. Thank you.

685
00:57:22,680 --> 00:57:25,320
I wanted everything to be
worthy of you and our family.

686
00:57:27,000 --> 00:57:28,480
You've done your motherly duty again.

687
00:57:30,160 --> 00:57:31,280
These are very precious.

688
00:57:38,120 --> 00:57:39,920
As long as you are happy, my son.

689
00:57:42,000 --> 00:57:43,760
I will do whatever needs to be done.

690
00:57:44,400 --> 00:57:45,400
But it's all for you.

691
00:57:45,920 --> 00:57:48,760
I don't care if the
Yıldırıms are happy or not.

692
00:57:49,680 --> 00:57:51,160
You know, truth be told.

693
00:57:56,040 --> 00:57:57,280
Excitement is at its peak, huh?

694
00:57:58,920 --> 00:58:01,200
I didn't expect to be this excited.

695
00:58:02,040 --> 00:58:03,040
I understand you...

696
00:58:03,360 --> 00:58:05,440
Even I am incredibly excited.

697
00:58:07,000 --> 00:58:08,920
Your face is smiling.
No one is happier than me.

698
00:58:10,040 --> 00:58:11,040
Thanks, Cemal.

699
00:58:11,600 --> 00:58:13,360
We'll get you married
soon too, God willing.

700
00:58:19,120 --> 00:58:20,120
So, if we're ready?

701
00:58:29,400 --> 00:58:30,400
-Malik. -Hmm?

702
00:58:31,240 --> 00:58:33,560
Mrs. Müzeyyen has spared no expense.

703
00:58:34,440 --> 00:58:35,440
What do you mean expense?

704
00:58:36,680 --> 00:58:38,800
Expense... Money, I mean.

705
00:58:38,840 --> 00:58:40,160
Come on, let's go.

706
00:59:15,240 --> 00:59:16,640
She's really gone all out.

707
00:59:21,320 --> 00:59:23,000
Well, wonders never cease…

708
00:59:24,360 --> 00:59:27,160
I don't know what to say.
I'm so surprised right now…

709
01:00:18,920 --> 01:00:19,920
You look beautiful.

710
01:00:22,480 --> 01:00:23,480
Thank you.

711
01:00:32,320 --> 01:00:34,400
Welcome. Please, come in.

712
01:00:39,280 --> 01:00:40,280
Go inside.

713
01:01:10,120 --> 01:01:12,240
Çiçek, you distribute the chocolates.

714
01:01:16,600 --> 01:01:18,240
Mr. Cemal, there's a problem.

715
01:01:24,800 --> 01:01:25,800
Come in.

716
01:01:25,880 --> 01:01:27,160
Thank you.

717
01:01:27,240 --> 01:01:29,080
-Enjoy. -Thank you.

718
01:01:31,520 --> 01:01:32,680
I love chocolate.

719
01:01:32,840 --> 01:01:34,840
-Let's have sweet talk. -I won't have any.

720
01:01:35,000 --> 01:01:36,000
Here you are.

721
01:01:38,000 --> 01:01:39,000
My favorite.

722
01:01:48,680 --> 01:01:50,600
It's customary to ask how you are.

723
01:01:51,320 --> 01:01:52,520
You seem well.

724
01:01:53,080 --> 01:01:55,160
Thank God. We are well, Mrs. Nermin.

725
01:01:56,000 --> 01:01:57,000
Good.

726
01:01:57,240 --> 01:01:58,400
May you always be better.

727
01:02:04,560 --> 01:02:05,920
How are you, Mrs. Zahide?

728
01:02:07,400 --> 01:02:08,680
Thank you.

729
01:02:10,680 --> 01:02:11,760
How are you, Mr. Ateş?

730
01:02:12,920 --> 01:02:14,200
Thanks, Yaşar. I'm fine.

731
01:02:14,880 --> 01:02:16,600
May you always be better. I am fine too.

732
01:02:25,000 --> 01:02:26,680
Everything is very beautiful.

733
01:02:27,080 --> 01:02:28,360
You've gone to a lot of trouble.

734
01:02:29,400 --> 01:02:31,360
Well... It's customary.

735
01:02:32,040 --> 01:02:33,520
We did what was necessary.

736
01:02:34,520 --> 01:02:36,520
Of course. Yes.

737
01:02:37,600 --> 01:02:39,080
One must follow the customs.

738
01:02:42,240 --> 01:02:43,240
Anyway...

739
01:02:44,360 --> 01:02:46,560
Anyway. My daughter, you make the coffees.

740
01:03:09,840 --> 01:03:10,880
Get out of my way!

741
01:03:13,000 --> 01:03:14,760
Special orders, you can't enter.

742
01:03:15,080 --> 01:03:16,200
I said move!

743
01:03:21,440 --> 01:03:22,520
You will move!

744
01:03:23,360 --> 01:03:25,000
Or you go get the one who gave the order!

745
01:03:34,040 --> 01:03:35,200
What are you doing!

746
01:03:38,680 --> 01:03:39,800
Put your guns down!

747
01:03:41,160 --> 01:03:42,480
I said put them down!

748
01:03:48,720 --> 01:03:49,720
Bravo, Demet!

749
01:03:50,440 --> 01:03:52,040
Is this how siblinghood works!

750
01:03:52,520 --> 01:03:55,200
They're going to ask for Mercan's
hand, and you don't even tell me!

751
01:03:55,560 --> 01:03:56,560
Brother, please!

752
01:03:57,440 --> 01:03:59,360
Please, come to your senses.

753
01:04:00,480 --> 01:04:02,040
Look, the end of this road is not good.

754
01:04:02,200 --> 01:04:03,200
Accept the situation.

755
01:04:03,560 --> 01:04:06,400
Forget Mercan, build your own life.

756
01:04:09,800 --> 01:04:10,800
What's going on here?

757
01:04:15,080 --> 01:04:16,080
You again?

758
01:04:17,240 --> 01:04:18,240
What are you saying, man?

759
01:04:20,480 --> 01:04:23,080
Please, don't cause any
trouble today, please.

760
01:04:24,600 --> 01:04:25,600
Cemal.

761
01:04:25,960 --> 01:04:27,240
My brother is leaving anyway.

762
01:04:28,400 --> 01:04:29,440
It'd be better if he left.

763
01:04:32,120 --> 01:04:33,120
Brother, please.

764
01:04:38,880 --> 01:04:39,880
Cemal.

765
01:04:40,880 --> 01:04:43,240
Don't let this man in, ever.
Good luck with your work.

766
01:04:45,400 --> 01:04:46,400
Okay, Demet.

767
01:04:55,000 --> 01:04:56,000
You'll see!

768
01:04:57,400 --> 01:04:58,880
Mercan, I won't give you to anyone!

769
01:04:59,880 --> 01:05:01,440
There is no other life for me!

770
01:05:03,080 --> 01:05:05,200
You will all understand…

771
01:05:30,440 --> 01:05:31,440
Where is Demet?

772
01:05:32,680 --> 01:05:34,040
She went outside, I think.

773
01:05:34,520 --> 01:05:37,560
You should have sat down. We would
have prepared and you could have come in?

774
01:05:38,400 --> 01:05:40,840
No, I'll do it.

775
01:05:41,560 --> 01:05:43,160
And I'll put plenty of bitterness in it.

776
01:05:53,600 --> 01:05:55,280
What happened, where did you disappear to?

777
01:05:57,280 --> 01:05:58,440
I went out for some air.

778
01:06:00,160 --> 01:06:01,760
I think I got a bit emotional.

779
01:06:03,960 --> 01:06:05,440
You've been through so much hardship.

780
01:06:06,840 --> 01:06:08,520
Now, seeing you happy like this...

781
01:06:09,560 --> 01:06:10,560
Come here...

782
01:06:16,600 --> 01:06:17,600
My dear.

783
01:06:22,480 --> 01:06:24,400
How's it going, any excitement?

784
01:06:25,480 --> 01:06:26,480
Of course…

785
01:06:30,360 --> 01:06:31,360
Okay.

786
01:06:42,480 --> 01:06:43,480
Yes.

787
01:06:49,040 --> 01:06:50,040
Bitter sauce...

788
01:06:53,960 --> 01:06:54,960
Mercan...

789
01:06:57,040 --> 01:06:58,040
Sour...

790
01:07:01,440 --> 01:07:02,440
And salt.

791
01:07:06,800 --> 01:07:07,800
Like life.

792
01:07:09,480 --> 01:07:10,480
Merciless.

793
01:07:11,480 --> 01:07:13,440
Oh, how is Mr. Ateş going to drink this?

794
01:07:13,920 --> 01:07:15,240
Isn't there something sweet?

795
01:07:18,320 --> 01:07:20,160
We'll add that to our lives together.

796
01:07:23,680 --> 01:07:24,680
With love, right.

797
01:07:26,280 --> 01:07:27,280
With love...

798
01:07:34,560 --> 01:07:37,840
We should actually put
this in Müzeyyen's coffee.

799
01:07:38,520 --> 01:07:39,520
No...

800
01:07:40,040 --> 01:07:43,200
She barely agreed to come,
I made hers extra sweet.

801
01:07:47,520 --> 01:07:48,520
Come on...

802
01:07:49,280 --> 01:07:50,280
Come on...

803
01:07:51,000 --> 01:07:52,000
Let's go then...

804
01:08:03,720 --> 01:08:05,800
-Here you are. -Thank you, my girl.

805
01:08:08,760 --> 01:08:10,960
-Thank you. -Enjoy.

806
01:08:19,360 --> 01:08:20,360
Here you are.

807
01:08:20,920 --> 01:08:21,920
Thank you.

808
01:08:22,720 --> 01:08:23,920
Mrs. Nermin.

809
01:08:24,360 --> 01:08:26,880
-Thank you, Çiçek. -Enjoy.

810
01:08:36,280 --> 01:08:37,560
You've done it now, haven't you?

811
01:08:38,560 --> 01:08:40,440
Everything will be according to tradition.

812
01:09:00,000 --> 01:09:01,840
Çiçek! Çiçek!

813
01:09:02,160 --> 01:09:04,320
You put the bitter and sour
in the coffee, didn't you?

814
01:09:04,840 --> 01:09:06,120
Oh, the poor thing!

815
01:09:06,800 --> 01:09:08,000
What do you mean, poor thing?

816
01:09:08,240 --> 01:09:09,496
Honestly, I didn't feel sorry at all.

817
01:09:09,520 --> 01:09:11,640
You did well. Good job.

818
01:09:29,400 --> 01:09:30,600
Enjoy your coffee, Mr. Ateş.

819
01:10:38,440 --> 01:10:39,440
Hello!

820
01:10:41,720 --> 01:10:43,560
Listen carefully. Soon,
hell will break loose.

821
01:10:45,600 --> 01:10:46,800
Gather men.

822
01:10:47,480 --> 01:10:48,480
Wait for my signal.

823
01:10:51,880 --> 01:10:52,880
Okay.

824
01:10:54,560 --> 01:10:56,880
Don't worry, I'll pay them double.

825
01:10:59,160 --> 01:11:00,440
As long as they do what I say.

826
01:11:02,360 --> 01:11:03,360
Wait for my signal.

827
01:11:10,520 --> 01:11:14,840
No matter how much you trample on
me, you won't be able to swallow me.

828
01:11:16,920 --> 01:11:18,760
Then you'll see who Nezir is!

829
01:11:31,720 --> 01:11:33,000
I always find another way.

830
01:12:10,240 --> 01:12:11,240
(clears throat)

831
01:12:26,600 --> 01:12:27,800
Well...

832
01:12:30,760 --> 01:12:32,120
You know our situation.

833
01:12:41,920 --> 01:12:44,240
By the command of God and
the word of the Prophet...

834
01:12:48,440 --> 01:12:50,400
I ask for Mercan's hand for my son Ateş.

835
01:13:02,560 --> 01:13:04,400
I ask for Mercan's hand for my son Ateş.

836
01:13:17,280 --> 01:13:18,840
Well, it was a bit sudden, of course…

837
01:13:23,760 --> 01:13:24,880
I don't know what to say.

838
01:13:31,520 --> 01:13:33,720
Will your son be able
to make my daughter happy?

839
01:13:46,040 --> 01:13:48,680
My daughter's happiness
is what matters to me.

840
01:13:53,560 --> 01:13:56,440
Since they love each other…

841
01:14:10,360 --> 01:14:11,480
I give my consent.

842
01:14:47,000 --> 01:14:48,000
May you always be happy.

843
01:14:50,880 --> 01:14:52,000
Congratulations, my dear.

844
01:14:59,200 --> 01:15:00,200
Mercan.

845
01:15:05,160 --> 01:15:06,160
Congratulations.

846
01:15:10,440 --> 01:15:11,600
Congratulations, Mrs. Mercan.

847
01:15:18,400 --> 01:15:19,400
Congratulations, my dear.

848
01:15:19,680 --> 01:15:22,760
Come on... Let's put on the rings.

849
01:15:36,240 --> 01:15:38,480
Cemal... You put on the rings.

850
01:15:39,960 --> 01:15:40,960
I'll put them on, mother.

851
01:15:45,320 --> 01:15:46,320
My brother...

852
01:15:50,360 --> 01:15:51,360
Mercan...

853
01:15:56,080 --> 01:15:57,640
The scissors won't cut...

854
01:16:01,440 --> 01:16:02,440
We'll manage.

855
01:16:19,240 --> 01:16:20,440
There we go.

856
01:17:30,440 --> 01:17:33,920
I will make you suffer what
you made me suffer, Ateş Karahan.

857
01:17:35,960 --> 01:17:36,960
All of it!

858
01:17:39,320 --> 01:17:40,560
Was the coffee too bitter?

859
01:17:42,400 --> 01:17:43,400
A little...

860
01:17:44,520 --> 01:17:46,000
But every drop is worth it right now.

861
01:17:52,400 --> 01:17:53,760
May God make you happy forever.

862
01:17:53,800 --> 01:17:54,800
Thank you.
